   Bldg 001, Room 342, BARC-WEST
   Beltsville MD 20705

   Mission:
   Research in the Sustainable Agricultural Systems Laboratory develops
   principles and practices to support the achievement of sustainable
   agroecosystems. A multidisciplinary team of scientists consisting of
   microbiologists, soil ecologists, weed scientists, plant physiologists,
   plant breeders and economists address fundamental problems that limit
   the development of sustainable farming systems. Research focuses on
   development of cover crop-based production systems, improved cultivars
   of cover crops, integrated weed management systems and biological pest
   control strategies as well as understanding the microbiological
   processes that improve the quality of soils and the molecular and
   biochemical mechanisms that improve the ability of crops to adapt to or
   resist the effects of environmental stress.

